[{"id":"55f49e80df2038fc90049de4987cf4a5","from":"Lesley Groff","from_email":"lesley@nysgllc.com","to":"J. Epstein","to_list":[{"name":"J. Epstein","email":"jeeproject@yahoo.com"}],"cc_list":[],"subject":"FW: MEETING WITH JEFFREY EPSTEIN ON TUESDAY, FEBRUARY 26 AT 5:30PM","date":"2008-02-25T21:46:31.000Z","formatted_date":"Feb 25, 2008","formatted_time":"9:46 PM","body":" \n\n \n\nFrom: egneurocog@aol.com [mailto:egneurocog@aol.com] \nSent: Monday, February 25, 2008 4:45 PM\nTo: Lesley Groff\nCc: Lesley Groff\nSubject: MEETING WITH JEFFREY EPSTEIN ON TUESDAY, FEBRUARY 26 AT 5:30PM\n\n \n\nDear Leslie,\n\n \n\nThis is the updated list of participants in our meeting tomorrow,\nTuesday February 26 at 5:30pm:\n\n \n\nYann LeCun, Ph.D. - Professor of Computer Science, NYU\n\n \n\nHakwan Lau, Ph.D. - Assistant Professor of Cognitive Neuroscience,\nColumbia Univ.\n\n \n\nThomas Thesen, Ph.D. - Assistant Professor of Neurology, NYU\n\n\nY Lan Boureau - doctoral student, Courant Institute, NYU\n\nMarc'Aurelio Ranzato - doctoral student, Courant Institute, NYU.\n\nWe all look forward to our meeting with Jeffrey.\n\nBest wishes,\n\n\nEG\n\nElkhonon Goldberg, Ph.D., ABPP\n\nClinical Professor of Neurology\nNew York University School of Medicine\n\nDiplomate\nAmerican Board of Professional Psychology\nin Clinical Neuropsychology\n\n315 West 57th Street\nSuite 401\nNew York, NY 10019\nUSA\n\ntel +1 212 541 6412\nfax +1 212 765 7158\negneurocog@aol.com\nelkhonon.goldberg@med.nyu.edu\nwww.elkhonongoldberg.com\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n________________________________\n\nMore new features than ever. Check out the new AOL Mail\n<http://o.aolcdn.com/cdn.webmail.aol.com/mailtour/aol/en-us/text.htm?nci\nd=aolcmp00050000000003> !\n\n","body_html":"<html xmlns:v=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:vml\" xmlns:o=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office\" xmlns:w=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word\" xmlns:x=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:excel\" xmlns:p=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:powerpo